nsproxy tests
====================

This directory contains integration tests for nsproxy. The integration test
suite consists of three core components:

1. Target Server
   A ping-pong server (tcp_pingpong.py, udp_pingpong.py) listens on port 37777.
   It receives data from the client and sends a response back.

2. Proxy Servers
   Support for 3proxy, v2ray, and sing-box as proxy servers.
   SOCKS5 proxy listens on 31080 (no auth) and 31081 (auth).
   HTTP proxy listens on 38080 (no auth) and 38081 (auth).

3. Application
   The ping-pong client that runs inside a network namespace via nsproxy.
   Its traffic is captured by nsproxy and forwarded through the proxy server.


REQUIREMENTS
----------

 - 3proxy OR v2ray OR sing-box (installed and in PATH)
 - Python 3 with pytest


USAGE
----------

Run following commands in the project root directory, not in tests/

To run all tests:
   pytest -v tests/

To run only normal tests (skip Valgrind):
   pytest -v -k "normal" tests/

To run only tests with specified proxy backend (e.g. singbox):
   pytest -v -k "singbox" tests/

To see detailed logs (including nsproxy verbose logs and Valgrind reports):
   pytest -v -s tests/

Note: nsproxy runs in verbose mode (`-vvv`) only when pytest is run with
verbose mode (`-v`).


VALGRIND TESTING
----------------

The Valgrind test suite is integrated into the standard pytest flow via 
parameterization.

To run Valgrind tests correctly, the project should be compiled without 
Address Sanitizer (ASan). Use the following build command:
  cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="-g -O0 -fno-omit-frame-pointer"
  cmake --build build
